  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Munich 1991: the Roots of the Current AI Boom",
      "url": "https://people.idsia.ch/~juergen/ai-boom-roots-munich-1991.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/n1xvd7",
      "score": 1,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "mpweiher",
      "published": "2026-06-22T12:09:39Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Sepp Hochreiter’s 1991 Munich diploma thesis first identified the vanishing gradient problem, a foundational barrier in training deep recurrent networks.",
        "This theoretical breakthrough under advisor Jürgen Schmidhuber directly enabled the development of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks in 1997.",
        "Solving vanishing gradients laid the groundwork for modern sequence modeling, directly influencing today's transformer architectures and large language models."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "help i accidentally a wigglegram",
      "url": "https://lmao.center/blog/wiggle-accidents/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/uuyjxb",
      "score": 55,
      "comments": 14,
      "author": "winter",
      "published": "2026-06-22T06:07:05Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Wigglegrams simulate 3D depth by looping sequential frames captured from slightly offset horizontal angles, mimicking stereoscopic camera perspectives.",
        "Programmatic alignment uses feature detection (SIFT/ORB) in OpenCV to calculate homography matrices, stabilizing frames around a common focal point.",
        "Aligned frames are compiled into looping GIFs or APNGs using tools like FFmpeg, ImageMagick, or Python's Pillow library."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Mark-of-the-web and pinning installers to sites",
      "url": "https://blog.randomoracle.io/2026/06/20/mark-of-the-web-and-pinning-installers-to-sites/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/z4vrld",
      "score": 9,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "raymii",
      "published": "2026-06-21T05:35:25Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Windows Mark-of-the-Web (MotW) uses NTFS Alternate Data Streams (Zone.Identifier) to flag untrusted downloads and trigger SmartScreen blocks.",
        "Pinning installers to specific download domains mitigates drive-by campaigns and prevents unauthorized execution of repackaged malicious binaries.",
        "Because threat actors bypass MotW via ISO or LNK files, defenders must enforce strict application control and code signing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I am dreading our LLM-written incident report future",
      "url": "https://surfingcomplexity.blog/2026/06/19/i-am-dreading-our-llm-written-incident-report-future/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ysxvko",
      "score": 42,
      "comments": 15,
      "author": "azhenley",
      "published": "2026-06-20T00:51:33Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLM-generated incident reports risk sanitizing critical technical details, turning valuable post-mortems into generic compliance theater rather than learning opportunities.",
        "Relying on LLMs to parse complex telemetry and logs can introduce hallucinations, masking actual infrastructure failures during post-mortem analysis.",
        "SRE teams must mandate human ownership of incident timelines and root-cause analysis to prevent AI-generated fluff from eroding engineering culture."
      ]
    },
